{
  "texts": [
    "In this paper we focus on real-time anomaly detection scenarios, and introduce a more robust criterion for evaluation based on real-time detection demands.",
    "All results and analysis are based on this setting.",
    "However, for offline detection tasks that do not have real-time requirements and require precise detection of the duration of anomalies, other evaluation criteria such as VUS [34] may be more suitable.",
    "You can specify this criterion as the evaluation criteria in TimeSeriesBench toolkit to obtain results that are more tailored to your specific application scenario.",
    "In this paper, we propose TimeSeriesBench, a comprehensive and application-oriented benchmark for evaluating the performance of existing and emerging UTS anomaly detection methods."
  ]
}